snippet.textDisplay: I thought this was an April Fools joke but I guess not.  The problem I have with this kind of collector is I don’t like when people collect cars and don’t use the cars.  Either use your cars or have them in a museum so others can enjoy.  I know it is his money and he could do what he wants.  Just my personal opinion on car collecting.  To see them with so much dust is kind of upsetting.  Why was there no car covers.  Just a horrible way to store very expensive and important cars.  I know Jay Leno keeps his cars very clean.  I would like to see Jay open a museum so others can enjoy like the Peterson Museum in Los Angeles.  The value of these cars is just ridiculous.  If he can afford these cars he can afford to have a full time or part time detailer and mechanic like Jay Leno has to take care of his cars.  All the cars should be moved out then the building and the building itself should get a deep cleaning then I would do a first wash on all the cars outside then bring them back in and do a complete detail on each of the cars.  At least you would have a cleaner environment to start with before the complete detailing.
